Sosi·la- ja dearvvasvuođaministeriija ja S·medikki gielladoaimmahat leat sivalaččat go Ohcejoga dearvvasvuođadoaibma ii leat almmuhan buot almmuhusaid s·megillii. D·t boaht· ovdan sosi·la- ja dearvvasvuođahoavda P‰ivi Salmisa čilgehusas vuođđodorvol·vdegodd·i.

Veh·dat·ittardeaddji Johanna Suurp‰‰ čielggadanbivdaga dihte Ohcejoga dearvvasvuođadoaibma ja oahpahusdoaibma fertejit v·stidit mo doaimmat ollaöuhttet S·mi giellal·ga. Gielda ii lihkostuvvan Sosi·la- ja dearvvasvuođahoavda P‰ivi Salminen lea v·lmmaötallan Vuođđodorvol·vdegotti v·st·dusa ja l·vdegoddi lea dohkkehan dan. V·st·dusas boaht· ovdan ahte dearvvasvuođadoaibma geahččala ieûas almmuhusaid almmustahttit s·me- ja suomagillii, muhto ii leat oll·sit lihkostuvvan. “ Praktihkas guovttegielatvuohta ollaöuhtto giellajorgalemiin, jorgalusat dahkkojuvvojit S·medikki gielladoaimmahagas. Gielladoaimmahaga uhc·naö resurssaid geaûil doaimmahat lea g·rtan prioriteret ieûas bargguid. D·t dieđus leamaöan resursav·tni lea maid dolvon dasa, ahte almmuhusat eai ·lo leat s·ddejuvvon gielladoaimmahahkii jorgaleapm·i,” P‰ivi Salminen dovddasta ieûas čilgehusas. Lohpida buoridit dili Salminen ·kkastall· ahte dilli lea d·l buoret go ovdal: “Gielladoaimmahaga bargidilli leamaöan čakčat 2009 buoret ja materi·la lea s·htt·n jorgalahttit eanet go ovdal, earret ear· influeansa A (H1N1)v –virusii lakt·seaddji r·vvagat ja almmuhusat sihke dearvvasvuođadoaimma skovit leat almmuhuvvon goapp·ge gillii. Almmuhusaid almmustahttima s·megillii lea oaivil buoridit d·s ovddosguvlui.” Ear·id sivva maid Salmisa oainnu mielde v·ilevaövuođat eai leat duööe S·medikki sivvan. Stuorra oasi dearvvasvuođaguovdd·ûa ·ööehasaide oaivvilduvvon broöyra-, r·va- ja diehtomateri·las leat buvttadan ear· l·g·dusat go gielda. Sosi·la- ja dearvvasvuođaministeriija, Dearvvasvuođa ja buorredili l·g·dus (Terveyden ja hyvinvoinnin laitos), organisaöuvnnat ja suorggi ear· doaibmit g·rvvistit materi·laset eanaö suomagillii. D·httu veahki ·ittardeaddjis Salminen fuom·öuhtt· ahte materi·la maid ear·t almmuhit, d·vj· leat ruoŧagillii maid, ja Vuođđodorvol·vdegoddi s·vv·, ahte veh·dat·ittardeaddji v·ikkuhivččii dasa, ahte st·hta sosi·la- ja dearvvasvuođadoaimma h·lddahussuorggit doaimmahivčče Ohcejoga gildii materi·la suoma- ja davvis·megillii.

Thinning or Thickening Walls?Thickened heart walls means that they are like an old Wellington boot and lose some of their flexibility; tnhnied heart walls is worse as muscle has died off and been replaced with scar tissue so that the heart can no longer pump properly. Eleven millimetres is the magic number and a wall thickness of 5-11 millimetres is ideal. The measurement is recorded on echocardiograms but the information tends to get withheld from patients. The result of these changes that occur from chronic heart strain is hypokinesis (reduced movement) that is perhaps recoverable to some degree; akinesis (no movement) that can possibly be compensated for by adjoining untethered heart muscle working harder; and dyskinesis (abnormal movement) that is incapable of recovery.
